"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"cc5208",
"children":[
"Consider catheter-related infection in any patient with bacteremia or fever and a central venous catheter. Purulence and cellulitis around the catheter site are specific, but not sensitive, for catheter-related infection. Obtain two sets of peripheral blood cultures from different sites before starting empiric antibiotic therapy."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s34_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"204989",
"children":[
"Remove the catheter, then:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fb78c0",
"children":[
"begin empiric antibiotics"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9dbb4f",
"children":[
"confirm clearance of bacteremia with follow-up blood cultures"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c7b8f5",
"children":[
"evaluate with echocardiography"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e0798e",
"children":[
"evaluate patients with candidemia for ",
{
"type":"tag",
